description: The pool will hold material, including cadmium and lead, dredged from Peel Marina, the government says.
title: Work on 'silt lagoon' for Peel Marina dredging to begin
title_page: Work on 'silt lagoon' for Peel Marina dredging to begin - BBC News
maintext: The work, which is necessary to maintain access to the berths in the marina, will be done in two stages - with the first 22,000 tonnes removed between March and May and the second across the same period in 2021.
